UPDATE modules SET description = 'EMP HRMS is the core human resource management system that powers the entire EmpCloud ecosystem. Included free with every EMP Cloud subscription, it provides essential HR operations that every organization needs to manage their workforce effectively. The module covers comprehensive employee profile management with extended personal details, emergency contacts, education history, work experience, dependents, and multiple addresses. It includes a powerful attendance management system with configurable shifts, geo-fencing for location-based check-ins, real-time attendance tracking, and a regularization workflow for corrections. The leave management system supports custom leave types, flexible accrual policies, multi-level approval workflows, a visual leave calendar, and compensatory off requests. Document management capabilities allow HR teams to organize, upload, verify, and track employee documents with expiry alerts and mandatory compliance tracking. Company-wide announcements can be targeted by department or role with read tracking and priority levels. The policy management system enables organizations to publish company policies with version history and track employee acknowledgments for compliance. EMP HRMS serves as the foundation for all other EMP modules. Employee data flows from here to Payroll, Performance, Recruit, and Exit modules. Built with enterprise-grade security including role-based access control, audit logging, and multi-tenant isolation. Whether you have 10 employees or 10,000, EMP HRMS scales to meet your HR operations needs with a clean, intuitive interface that both HR administrators and employees love to use.' WHERE slug = 'emp-hrms';

UPDATE modules SET description = 'EMP Payroll is a comprehensive payroll management system designed for businesses operating across India, the United States, and the United Kingdom. It handles the complete payroll lifecycle from salary structure creation through computation, approval, and disbursement, with full audit trails at every step. For Indian businesses, it provides built-in compliance with PF, ESI, TDS, and Professional Tax across multiple states including Karnataka, Maharashtra, Tamil Nadu, and more. The system supports both Old and New tax regimes with automatic Section 87A rebate calculation, surcharge, marginal relief, and health and education cess. US payroll covers federal income tax withholding based on W-4, FICA including Social Security and Medicare, state taxes for all 50 states, and FUTA. UK payroll handles PAYE with cumulative and non-cumulative basis, National Insurance contributions, Student Loan deductions across all plan types, and auto-enrollment pension. The salary structure builder allows flexible CTC breakdown with configurable components including Basic, HRA, Special Allowance, LTA, and custom components. Payslip generation produces detailed HTML payslips with company branding, comprehensive earnings and deductions breakdown, and year-to-date summaries. Bank transfer file generation supports NEFT and RTGS CSV format for direct salary credits. The analytics dashboard provides cost trend analysis, month-over-month comparisons, headcount charts, and department-wise cost breakdowns with automated variance alerts for anomalies like zero net pay or unusually high deductions.' WHERE slug = 'emp-payroll';

UPDATE modules SET description = 'EMP Billing is a full-featured, open-source billing and invoicing platform that handles the complete billing lifecycle from quotes through invoices, payments, receipts, and financial reports. Think of it as an open-source alternative to Zoho Invoice and Zoho Books, built specifically for the EmpCloud ecosystem. It supports multi-country tax compliance with dedicated tax engines for Indian GST including CGST, SGST, IGST with HSN and SAC codes and e-Invoice support, UAE VAT and Corporate Tax, EU and UK VAT with reverse charge mechanism for cross-border B2B transactions, and US Sales Tax across all 50 states with county and city tax stacking. The invoicing system supports multi-tax line items, auto-numbering sequences, partial payments, credit note application, and professional PDF generation. Quotes can be versioned, sent for client approval through the client portal, and converted to invoices with one click. Payment processing integrates with Stripe for cards and ACH, Razorpay for Indian payment methods including UPI and netbanking, and PayPal via REST API. Recurring invoices can be scheduled daily, weekly, monthly, or yearly with auto-send and auto-charge capabilities. The subscription management system supports plan tiers, trial periods, usage-based billing, and quantity-based seat licensing. A full client portal allows customers to view invoices and quotes, make payments online, approve quotes, raise disputes, and download statements independently.' WHERE slug = 'emp-billing';

UPDATE modules SET description = 'EMP Monitor is an advanced employee activity and productivity monitoring platform that provides real-time insights into how your workforce operates. It enables managers and HR leaders to understand work patterns, optimize productivity, and make data-driven decisions about resource allocation and team performance. The platform captures detailed activity data including application and website usage, active versus idle time tracking, and productivity scoring based on configurable categories. Screenshots can be captured at configurable intervals with blur options for privacy-sensitive content. The real-time dashboard shows who is currently active, what applications they are using, and their productivity scores throughout the day. Detailed timeline views let managers see exactly how each team member spent their working hours broken down by productive, unproductive, and neutral activities. The reporting engine generates comprehensive reports including productivity trends over time, team comparisons, department-level analytics, and individual performance summaries. Automated alerts notify managers when employees fall below productivity thresholds or exhibit unusual activity patterns. The system respects employee privacy with configurable monitoring levels from lightweight time tracking to detailed activity capture and clearly communicates monitoring policies to employees. Data retention policies can be configured per organization to comply with local privacy regulations including GDPR and other data protection laws. EMP Monitor integrates seamlessly with EMP Cloud for authentication and user management, and provides data feeds to EMP Performance for inclusion in performance reviews and productivity assessments.' WHERE slug = 'emp-monitor';

UPDATE modules SET description = 'EMP Recruit is a modern applicant tracking and recruitment management system that streamlines the entire hiring process from job posting to onboarding. It provides a complete ATS with a visual Kanban pipeline that moves candidates through customizable stages: Applied, Screened, Interview, Offer, and Hired. HR teams can create detailed job postings with requirements, salary ranges, experience levels, and remote work policies, then publish them to a branded public career page that reflects organization branding and culture. The candidate management system maintains a searchable talent database with resume parsing, contact details, experience tracking, and source attribution. Interview scheduling supports multiple round types including phone screens, video calls, onsite interviews, technical assignments, and panel interviews with multiple interviewers. Each interviewer submits structured feedback through customizable scorecards with ratings per competency, strengths, weaknesses, and a hire recommendation. The offer management workflow includes multi-level approval chains, offer letter generation from templates, and tracking of offer acceptance or decline with detailed reasons. Once a candidate is hired, the onboarding module activates template-based checklists covering document collection, IT equipment setup, training schedules, team introductions, and welcome activities. Tasks are assigned to relevant team members with due dates and progress tracking. The referral program allows employees to refer candidates with bonus tracking and eligibility management. Recruitment analytics provide insights into time-to-hire metrics, source effectiveness, pipeline conversion rates, and offer acceptance rates.' WHERE slug = 'emp-recruit';

UPDATE modules SET description = 'EMP Field is a comprehensive field force management platform designed for organizations with employees working outside traditional office environments including sales teams, service technicians, delivery personnel, and field agents. The core GPS check-in system allows field workers to record their location when starting and ending work at client sites or job locations, with optional photo proof for verification and timestamp accuracy. Geo-fencing creates virtual boundaries around work zones and client sites, automatically detecting when employees enter or leave designated areas and triggering real-time alerts for managers. Live location tracking displays all field workers on a real-time interactive map with breadcrumb trails showing their movement throughout the day. The work order system enables managers to create, assign, and prioritize field tasks with location details, estimated durations, and detailed instructions. Workers receive assignments on their mobile-optimized interface and can update status, add completion notes, and capture photos of finished work. Route planning helps organize daily visits efficiently, with optional premium route optimization that calculates the shortest path between multiple stops using advanced algorithms. Expense tracking covers field-related costs including travel, food, materials, and accommodation with receipt upload and multi-level approval workflows. Automatic mileage calculation computes distance traveled using GPS tracks and calculates reimbursement amounts based on configurable per-kilometer rates. The analytics dashboard provides insights into field productivity, travel versus work time ratios, visit completion rates, and SLA compliance. Offline mode ensures field workers can continue logging activities without internet connectivity.' WHERE slug = 'emp-field';

UPDATE modules SET description = 'EMP Performance is the performance and career management module that enables organizations to build a culture of continuous feedback, goal alignment, and professional development. It supports multiple review cycle types including quarterly reviews, annual appraisals, mid-year check-ins, 360-degree feedback, and probation reviews, each with configurable deadlines for self-assessment, manager review, and peer feedback phases. The goals and OKR system allows employees to set individual, team, department, and company-level objectives with measurable key results, progress tracking, and weighted scoring. Goals can be cascaded from organizational objectives down to individual contributors, ensuring strategic alignment across the entire company. Competency frameworks define the skills and behaviors expected at each role and level, providing the foundation for structured performance evaluations. During review cycles, employees complete self-assessments rating themselves against defined competencies, managers provide their evaluations with detailed qualitative feedback, and peers submit 360-degree reviews through a nomination and approval workflow. The calibration and bell curve tools help HR leaders ensure rating consistency across departments and managers, preventing grade inflation. Performance Improvement Plans provide a structured process for addressing underperformance with clear objectives, timelines, regular check-ins, and documented outcomes. Career path management defines progression ladders with competency requirements at each level, helping employees understand their growth trajectory and identify skill gaps. One-on-one meeting tools help managers maintain regular touchpoints with agenda management, action item tracking, and recurring scheduling capabilities.' WHERE slug = 'emp-performance';

UPDATE modules SET description = 'EMP Rewards is an employee recognition and rewards platform that helps organizations build a culture of appreciation, boost morale, and improve retention through peer-to-peer recognition, gamification, and tangible rewards. The core peer recognition system enables any employee to send kudos to colleagues, highlighting specific achievements and tagging organizational values like teamwork, innovation, leadership, and customer focus. Kudos appear on a public celebration wall where coworkers can react with likes, claps, and hearts, and add congratulatory comments creating a vibrant social experience. The points system awards points for giving and receiving recognition, earning badges, and reaching milestones, with all transactions tracked in a transparent ledger that employees can review anytime. Badges and achievements provide visual recognition for milestones like first kudos received, one-year work anniversary, top performer of the quarter, and custom organizational achievements defined by HR. Badges can be auto-awarded based on configurable criteria or manually granted by managers and HR administrators. The reward catalog offers redeemable items including gift cards, extra PTO days, company merchandise, unique experiences, and charitable donations, all priced in points with inventory management. Manager nomination programs support formal recognition such as Employee of the Month and Innovation Awards with structured nomination, review, and selection processes. Department and organization-wide leaderboards gamify recognition with weekly, monthly, quarterly, and annual rankings. Budget management tools let organizations set recognition spending limits per manager or department with utilization tracking and real-time reporting dashboards.' WHERE slug = 'emp-rewards';

UPDATE modules SET description = 'EMP Biometrics is an advanced biometric verification module that strengthens employee security and accuracy through seamless integration of biometric authentication into HR workflows. The facial recognition system enables contactless attendance marking where employees simply look at a camera to record their check-in and check-out times, eliminating buddy punching and time theft that plague traditional attendance systems. Liveness detection technology ensures that real human faces are being scanned rather than photographs, videos, or masks, maintaining the integrity of the entire verification process. The module supports multiple biometric modalities including facial recognition as the primary method, with extensible adapter hooks for fingerprint scanners and iris recognition readers through a standardized interface. Multi-device support allows organizations to deploy biometric terminals at multiple office locations, entrance gates, and restricted access points, all synchronized through a central cloud dashboard in real-time. Each device captures location data alongside biometric readings, enabling automatic geo-tagged attendance records tied to specific office locations, buildings, or floor levels. Visitor management capabilities extend biometric check-in to guests, contractors, and temporary workers with pre-registration workflows, automatic host notification, digital badge creation, and check-out reminders. Access control integration connects with physical security systems to manage door access permissions, restricted area entry authorization, and floor-level access based on employee roles, departments, and security clearance levels. The module integrates with EMP Attendance for automatic time tracking and EMP Cloud for unified identity verification.' WHERE slug = 'emp-biometrics';

UPDATE modules SET description = 'EMP Exit is a comprehensive exit and portfolio management module that simplifies the complex process of employee offboarding while maintaining compliance, protecting organizational knowledge, and preserving positive relationships with departing employees. The module handles every aspect of the exit lifecycle from resignation acceptance through full and final settlement disbursement. Configurable exit checklists can be customized per department, role, and exit type including resignation, termination, retirement, end of contract, and mutual separation, with automatic task assignment to relevant stakeholders across the organization. The multi-department clearance workflow ensures sign-off from IT, Finance, HR, Administration, and the reporting manager before an exit is finalized, with configurable approval chains and automatic escalation rules for delayed approvals. Structured exit interviews capture valuable organizational feedback through customizable question templates covering reasons for leaving, satisfaction ratings across multiple dimensions, improvement suggestions, and rehire willingness assessment. The full and final settlement calculator automatically computes pending salary on a pro-rata basis, leave encashment based on balance and daily rate, gratuity for eligible employees with five or more years of service, notice period recovery or waiver amounts, outstanding loan deductions, tax implications, and asset damage charges. Asset return tracking ensures all company property including laptops, mobile phones, ID cards, and access cards is returned and verified with condition documentation. Knowledge transfer management assigns successors, creates structured handover documentation checklists, and tracks completion. Letter generation produces experience letters, relieving letters, and service certificates from customizable Handlebars templates.' WHERE slug = 'emp-exit';

UPDATE modules SET description = 'EMP Projects is a project management and time tracking module designed for organizations that need to plan, execute, and monitor projects while accurately tracking the time and effort invested by team members across multiple initiatives. The module provides a comprehensive project workspace with interactive task boards, Gantt chart timelines, and calendar views that give managers complete visibility into project progress, dependencies, and team workload distribution. Projects can be organized with hierarchical task structures including milestones, epics, user stories, and subtasks, each with assignees, due dates, priority levels, and status tracking through customizable workflow stages that match your team process. Time tracking enables employees to log hours against specific tasks and projects with timer-based tracking for real-time capture during work and manual entry for retrospective time logging. Timesheet management provides weekly and monthly views for employees to review and submit their logged hours, with configurable manager approval workflows suitable for both internal tracking and client billing scenarios. Resource allocation tools help managers plan team capacity across projects, identify overloaded or underutilized team members, and make informed staffing and hiring decisions based on actual utilization data. Project budgets can be configured with hourly rates per role or team member, and the system tracks actual cost versus planned budget in real-time with automated variance alerts when projects approach or exceed their budgets. Sprint planning supports agile teams with iteration planning, velocity tracking, burndown charts, and retrospective documentation. EMP Projects integrates with EMP Billing for automatic client invoice generation.' WHERE slug = 'emp-projects';

UPDATE modules SET description = 'EMP Attendance is a comprehensive attendance tracking and leave management module that forms the foundation of workforce time management for organizations with complex scheduling needs. While basic attendance features are included free with EMP HRMS, EMP Attendance provides advanced capabilities for organizations with multiple locations, rotating shifts, and sophisticated leave policies. The shift management system supports unlimited custom shifts with configurable start and end times, break durations, grace periods for late arrivals and early departures, and night shift handling with automatic cross-day calculations. Shift rostering enables managers to create weekly and monthly rotation schedules, assign employees to rotating shift patterns, and handle swap requests between team members with approval workflows. The attendance capture system supports multiple input sources including manual web-based check-in, biometric device integration through standardized APIs, mobile GPS-based check-in with geo-fencing validation against configured office locations, and bulk import capabilities via CSV files or REST API integration from third-party HR and access control systems. Attendance regularization provides a structured workflow for employees to request corrections to their attendance records with detailed reason documentation and multi-level manager approval, maintaining a complete audit trail of all modifications. The leave management system includes advanced features such as pro-rated leave allocation for mid-year joiners, automatic monthly and quarterly accrual based on configurable schedules, carry-forward rules with expiration dates and maximum limits, leave encashment calculations, sandwich rule configurations for leaves taken adjacent to holidays, and restricted holiday selection from a predefined list.' WHERE slug = 'emp-attendance';
